===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Chatsworth had a population of 75, with 28 households and 19 families residing in the city. The median age was 44.5 years. 25.3% of residents were under the age of 18, and 13.3% were 65 years of age or older. The population distribution by broader age groups was 30.7% under age 20, 8.0% from ages 20 to 24, 12.0% from ages 25 to 44, 36.0% from ages 45 to 64, and 13.3% ages 65 and older. The gender makeup of the city was 58.7% male and 41.3% female. For every 100 females, there were 141.9 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 143.5 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A12945&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A12945&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A12945&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 28 households, 35.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them. Of all households, 46.4% were married-couple households, 7.1% were cohabiting-couple households, 25.0% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present, and 21.4% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present. Non-families accounted for 32.1% of households. About 25.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 0.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 39 housing units, with a population density of 150.8 inhabitants per square mile (58.2/km<sup>2</sup>) and a housing-unit density of 78.4 per square mile (30.3/km<sup>2</sup>). Of housing units, 28.2% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 3.6%, and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

